<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written Evidence from the Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport (UK) Cymru Wales</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Written Evidence from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> the Chartered Institute of Logistics and Transport (UK) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Cymru</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> Wales </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">(TIC 050)</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Wales</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> has a number of good examples of how isolated communities can be serviced by public transport</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Traws </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Cymru network will provide a long distance, high quality bus service between isolated communities and major centres.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bwcabus provides demand responsive travel, significantly increasing passenger numbers and reducing subsidy</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Community transport remains a ch</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">allenge, as it is often perceived as not being part of the transport network</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Integrated ticketing between bus and train can make passenger’s journeys easier</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Access to isolated areas is an important, but sometimes overlooked area of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">transport provision. Within Wales, there is much experience in providing services to such communities, particularly in a rural context. It is some of these experiences that we wish to draw to the committee’s attention as examples that could be applied else</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">where.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Traws Cymru long distance bus services</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Within Wales, one of the challenges has been providing a public transport network to connect the country as a whole. The existing rail network is largely orientated around horizontal corridors across the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">north, middle and south, and consequently and journeys between them can be long and circuitous. While the demand for bus services may also be insufficient to fully cover operating costs, there is an important social benefit in achieving this connectivity.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As a result, the Welsh Government has been supporting the introduction of a high quality bus network branded Traws Cymru which, over time, will provide a network across Wales. The buses required for operating these services have been procured by the Welsh</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Government, with commercial operators then receiving a subsidy for their operation. The buses are equipped with leather seats and wifi, to provide an enhanced passenger experience.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The longest running route has been the T4, which connects Cardiff and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Newtown on a broadly 2 hourly basis.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> One feature of this service is that, by working with the operator, Stagecoach, the service has been integrated into the 15-minute frequency commercial service between Merthyr and Cardiff. This increases the utilisation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the buses while also avoiding the need for subsidy along the whole route.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The second route is the T9, connecting central Cardiff with the airport. Historically, the airport has suffered from poor surface access and, in order to encourage a growth in pa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ssenger numbers, the Welsh Government has introduced the T9 service. Previously, the airport was served by a longer route that operated at an irregular frequency and with timings that did not align with the flight schedule. The new service operates every 2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">0 minutes from 4am until midnight. This level of service could not be supported commercially currently, but reflects a policy decision to reduce the isolation of the airport. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Bwcabus – local, demand responsive transport</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">At a more local level, the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Bwcabus service in Carmarthenshire is an example of effective demand responsive transport. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The bus operates within a predefined region and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">links local villages as well as connecting to longer distance services to major towns. P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">otential passengers book </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">thei</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r journey </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in advance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This can be at short notice, with deadlines of 7pm </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for the next morning</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">11.30am for the same afternoon. The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">flexibility that this service provides has led to a significant growth in passenger numbers,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and offers many places substa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ntially more services per day than with previously. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As a result</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, there are certain times where the buses are now full. In terms of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the subsidy required, it has been stated that this is £2 per passenger, compared to £6 per passenger for the services Bwcabus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> replaced. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">More information on Bwcabws can be found here: </span><a href="http://www.bwcabus.traveline-cymru.info/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bwcabus.traveline-cymru.info/</span></a></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Community transport</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We note that the Committee is also interested in community transport. This </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">was an issue considered recently by the Enterprise and Business Committee of the Welsh Government.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> They identified a number of issues with which we would concur. Firstly, they highlighted that community transport services are often not effectively integrat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed with other public transport services. Consequently, they are not included within transport policies, despite the important role that they often perform in isolated communities (both rural and urban).</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Another point they raise is funding, where community transport services have suffered as a result of budget cuts. This is affecting both the level of service required and investment decisions for the providers. Including community transport within wider tr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ansport policies would ensure that decision making for the services could be considered in conjunction with other transport services to identify the best solution overall for the community. This may also allow community transport providers to deliver some </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">commercial bus services where appropriate. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Integrated ticketing</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Finally, a challenge for transport in isolated communities is providing end-to-end ticketing solutions, given that the journeys are often multi-modal in nature. In Wales, the Cymru</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Connect ticket enables a through bus/rail ticket to be booked to or from specific towns within Wales. Elsewhere, a number of operators in mid Wales (bus and rail) have come together to offer  a combined ticket for travel between Aberystwyth and Machynllet</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">h, whereby you can go out by bus and return by train (or vice versa). This integrated approach improves options for passengers.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Within Wales, there is much experience and good practice in providing transport solutions for isolated communities. These solutions are transferable to other operating environments, and therefore could be suitable for use elsewhere within the UK. We hope t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">hat highlighting these examples to the Committee will show that providing services to isolated communities is not a problem, but a challenge that can be overcome with appropriate support from policy makers and operators.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">While recognising the remit of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> committee’s enquiry, we would encourage consideration of the implications for logistics operations as well, where the increased cost of fuel is making deliveries in these regions more challenging. It may be that opportunities exist for passenger and freig</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ht transport to coexist on the same services, to overcome some of these challenges.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>